---
description: Enforce required metadata comments on agent code edits
globs:
  - "**/*.js"
  - "**/*.pug"
alwaysApply: true
---

# Comment Policy (Auto-Applied)

- When editing a file, add at least one short metadata comment near the changed logic.
- Metadata comment format must include:
  - date
  - agent model
  - short scope description
  - short hash token
- Use comment syntax that matches the file type:
  - JavaScript: `// YYYY-MM-DD, <model>: <scope> [<hash>]`
  - Pug: `//- YYYY-MM-DD, <model>: <scope> [<hash>]`
- *Pug line comments not allowed in expression (Inside brackets)
- Always duplicate metadata comments at the bottom of the same file, with these constraints:
  - The bottom block must contain the exact same metadata comment lines used near changed logic (character-for-character match).
  - The duplicated lines must appear as one contiguous block (no blank lines or non-metadata lines between them).
  - The first line of this bottom block must start no more than three lines after the final non-comment code line in the file.
- If the file is newly created by the agent, include one brief header comment at the top explaining purpose.
- Keep comments concise and factual; do not add verbose process logs.
